enhanced_by.reason: The selectXpath method requires a W3C Document or Node, which is typically created by converting a jsoup Element using fromJsoup.
The convert method is used to convert a jsoup Element to a W3C Document, which is a prerequisite for the selectXpath method.
The sourceNodes method retrieves the original jsoup nodes from the W3C nodes returned by selectXpath, allowing for assertions on the original jsoup nodes.
The asString method can serialize the W3C Document to a String, which can be used to assert the structure or content of the document after applying the XPath query.
